properties.name: Taipei National University of the Arts
properties.description: Posted by Philipleets    TNUA’s highest ideal is to work upon the foundation of traditional culture, learning from and integrating the arts and cultures of different peoples for the development of modern Chinese art. This is the goal for the school’s administrative operations and teaching. Therefore, the curriculum incorporates the Chinese and the West, the traditional and the modern, so as to carry on an integrated heritage. It is exploring the role of Chinese art in the development of modern culture, in an attempt to establish its lineage. For research and creativity, it enables a multi-style and multi-aspect environment that at the same time is closely connected to the spirit of Chinese culture. This goal is exactly the serious mission of the country’s professional arts education. On August 1, 2006, Prof. Ju Tzong-Ching was elected as TNUA president. The school will continue to build upon its present facilities and achievements in its teaching, research, performances and exhibitions. TNUA also aims to break new ground. In academic activities, TNAU aims to add new dimensions to tradition, giving students wider choices in their course of training. The school will introduce more resources from the outside, allowing academic and practical matters to co-develop at the same time. For international exchanges, TNUA is devising a global strategy to get it on a global track, in hopes to turn TNUA into a highly internationalized institution for the arts. Improvements will also be made to the curriculum and facilities, so as to make better use of its present resources. As the integration of culture and tourism is an inevitable trend, TNUA plans to set up an arts and cultural center for northern Taipei. TNUA will also continue promoting the university excellence project, strengthening its academic research, expanding its resources, raising TNUA’s social value and steering TNUA towards becoming a first-rate international university of the arts.

properties.name: 八里十三行博物館
properties.description: Posted by Philipleets  The establishment of the Shihsanhang Museum of Archaeology can be traced back to “rescue excavation work” undertaken at the Shihsanhang Site in 1990. At that time the Taiwan Provincial Government’s Department of Housing and Development planned to build a sewage treatment plant in the area. As a result, a group of noted archaeologists launched a campaign to save the Shihsanhang Site, which quickly received wide public support. This successfully resulted in the area being designated a Historical Site - Second class and part of the original site was ordered preserved. In 1992 the Executive Yuan ordered Taipei County government to establish a Shihsanhang Site Exhibition Room to display objects unearthed in the area. In 1998 this was renamed the Shihsanhang Museum of Archaeology and given the central objectives of preserving and displaying artifacts unearthed at the Shihsanhang Site, serving as an archaeology museum for all of northern Taiwan and an educational center, teaching people about the importance of the area. After its official opening in 2003, the Museum has also become an Ecomuseum of the Bali Left Bank.

properties.description: Posted by Philipleets 「圓山草堂」座落於三芝鄉圓山頂藝術村，由畫家王昭權和陶藝家陳佳慧夫妻共同經營。在兩名藝術家的巧手妝點下，圓山草堂就像聳立山間的一幅印象派畫作，綠意盎然的花園景緻，隨著光影不斷游移變化，散發濃厚的難以言喻的藝術氣息。民眾不但可以在這裡飽覽精彩的藝術作品，更可以享用主人精心提供的可口餐點。

properties.name: 新生公園Xinsheng park
properties.description: Posted by Philipleets  通常愛看飛機的遊客們，總是擠在松山機場後的小徑，邊閃著來車，邊體驗臨場感的視聽震憾！雖然刺激，但總是有許多不便！這裡推薦您一個色、香、味、聞俱全的好去處。 位於新生北路三段１０５號的新生公園，佔地約２０公頃，屬北市第二大公園，卻比青年公園更顯遼闊。這是因為它週邊環境為遠山繚繞，四周為新生高架橋、民族東路、松江路、濱江街，無市區繁華處的高廈林立，得以視覺上的開放！而園中花檀處處，搭配得宜，更是花香撲鼻！最妙的是，鄰邊的松山機場使得此處經常機聲隆隆，大約平均５至６分鐘可看到一架飛機降落！您可以吃著野餐，躺在草坪或樹蔭下，盡情觀賞眼前美景與震耳的樂音，保證心情為之一快！

properties.name: 林安泰古厝
properties.description: Posted by Philipleets  In the 19th Year of Chien Lung Period in Ching Dynasty（in1754 Lin,Chin-Ming（also known as Lin Yao-Kung), a native from An His City of Fukien Province, had led his families to sail across the Strait to Taiwan. First settled at Tamshui, then moved to Linkuo Chuang. Through trying very hard to be industrious and thrifty, he had finally bought some farming lands and real estates. Due to being good at business operation, his fourth son Lin, Chin-Neng（also known as Lin, Hui-Kung）had opened a "Jung Tai Shop" in Mengchia operating a shipping company and a grocery store to engage in import and export trade, then and there, his business was very successful. After accumulating his wealth, he had built a big house at where No.141 of Szuwei Rd. lies now. The main building of this house was completed in about the 48th to 50th Year of Chien Lung Period in Ching Dynas（1783~1785）. In the 2nd to 3rd Year of Tao Kuang Period in Ching Dynasty（1822~1823） the "Hu Long" in its both sides had been finished one after another. In order to remember hometown and think of his origin, Lin, Hui-kung had named his house as "An Tai", with "An" named after An Hsi City of Fukien Province and "Tai" after "Jung Tai Shop". It has been one of the oldest house existed in Taipei City for now.

properties.name: 滬尾砲台公園(HUWEI FORT Park)
properties.description: Posted by Philipleets   The construction of Huwei Fort started in the 12 th year of Guang-Shy reign (1886). Believing that taking enemy\'s strength can subdue them, Governor Liu hired a German engineer, Max E. Hecht, to oversee the construction project. Hecht\'s architectural design is based on western forts. He also employed battery experts for testing. The construction completed in the 15 th year Guang-Shy reign (1889). The fort has never been used in any war and remains intact.

properties.description: Posted by Philipleets 「行天宮」俗稱恩主宮廟，供奉的是三國時候的關公關雲長，民間商人敬為財神而軍人則奉為武神，位於民權東路2段的行天宮，1967年所建立的，建築物整體莊嚴樸實，正店門匾上有于右任所書行天宮三個大字，正門5座只有在春秋兩季迎神時才會開放，殿前的天公爐造型獨特，兩旁有飛騰龍形提耳，四端猶如伸展的龍頭蓄勢待發，廟內不設功德箱也禁止供奉牲禮，還免費供應祭拜香燭，首開傳統宗教界素心之風，行天宮以靈驗著稱香客眾多，廟中香火鼎盛，在鄰近的地下商場也因此而生意興隆。此處之行天宮係關渡分寺
